title: deeplabcut.check_labels: Attention: 'video...' does not appear to have labeled data!
body:
**Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version**

Windows 10, with an Anaconda Env, & DeepLabCut 2.0.7.
Browser: chrome

**Describe the problem**

After labeling all the extracted frames, I tried to run deeplabcut.check_labels(), but I got the message:

In [5]: deeplabcut.check_labels(r'D:\Mouse_top_view-Goldberg lab-2019-06-30\config.yaml')
Creating images with labels by Goldberg lab.
Attention: D:\Mouse_top_view-Goldberg lab-2019-06-30 lab-2019-06-30\labeled-data\cam12019-06-17T14_08_27 does not appear to have labeled data!
................. (for all videos)
and obviously the function does not create a 'labeled' directory with labeled frames.

**Screenshots**

![Picture1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52376512/60397136-48a66a00-9b52-11e9-9de1-1169a45d1ec4.png)
![Picture2](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52376512/60397175-c2d6ee80-9b52-11e9-9c43-4a2c6859dfb0.png)
![Picture3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52376512/60397183-f31e8d00-9b52-11e9-8fc9-8e4124a3072e.png)

**Additional context**

The config file path is correct.
I tried to re-label the same frames and when I load them to the GUI everything seems to be labeled. (3rd screenshot)
The .csv and .h5 files exist in all the directories. It seems that the labels do exist but the function cannot read the files.

How can I fix this?
